Several open-source Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers exist to connect AI assistants to the Shopify Admin API, including options like aserper/shopify-mcp [1], benwmerritt/shopify-mcp [2], and daanjonk/shopify-mcp [3]. These servers provide tools to manage products, orders, customers, inventory, and metafields using natural language [1][3][4].

To use one, you must first create a Custom App in your Shopify Admin settings to generate an Admin API access token [1][3][5]. You then configure the MCP server by providing your store domain and access token as environment variables [1][2][3].

Example configuration for a local MCP client:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "shopify": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "shopify-mcp",
        "--accessToken",
        "<YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN>",
        "--domain",
        "<YOUR_SHOP>.myshopify.com"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
[2] 

For remote use with platforms like Claude.ai, you typically deploy the server (e.g., via Railway) and add the public URL to your AI client's integration settings [3][4].
